%md
# Analysis
- `wdi_csv_text` use LazySimpleSerDe which split the line by comma, without knowing that it is splitting an extra comma in the second line, which in turn is splitting extra columns. 
- We use Hive CSV SerDe that is more powerful and smarter than LazySimpleSerDe. 
- Create a new HIVE table using OpenCSVSerDe on GS data and export the data to HDFS location using another HIVE table.

msg.data:
Analysis

  • wdi_csv_text use LazySimpleSerDe which split the line by comma, without knowing that it is splitting an extra comma in the second line, which in turn is splitting extra columns.
  • We use Hive CSV SerDe that is more powerful and smarter than LazySimpleSerDe.
  • Create a new HIVE table using OpenCSVSerDe on GS data and export the data to HDFS location using another HIVE table.

paragraphs.text:
-- HQL - It took 1 min and 44 seconds to execute
SELECT wdi_csv_parquet.indicatorvalue AS value, 
       wdi_csv_parquet.year           AS year, 
       wdi_csv_parquet.countryname    AS country 
FROM   (SELECT Max(indicatorvalue) AS ind, 
               countryname 
        FROM   wdi_csv_parquet 
        WHERE  indicatorcode = 'NY.GDP.MKTP.KD.ZG' 
               AND indicatorvalue <> 0 
        GROUP  BY countryname) t1 
       INNER JOIN wdi_csv_parquet 
               ON t1.ind = wdi_csv_parquet.indicatorvalue 
                  AND t1.countryname = wdi_csv_parquet.countryname
